instance virtual_to_physical_interaction : DTDFVocab:VirtualToPhysical [
    base:desc "Services such as Trajectory Generator and Continuous Validation publish target motor positions or speed requests to the MQTT broker; the Physical Crane Interface subscribes, translates them into serial commands, and forwards them to the TMC4671 motor drivers, thereby actuating the cart and hoist motors. Sensor feedback may also be queried from the physical hardware via the Interface."
]

instance twinning_time_scale : DTDFVocab:TimeScale [
    base:desc "All services operate on a continuous, real‑time time‑scale: logging and validation run at the update frequency of the physical sensors (typically tens of Hz), trajectory generation and simulation are invoked on operator commands or at a scheduled interval, and the MQTT broker delivers messages with negligible latency (< 100 ms) within the local Docker network."
]

instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
    base:desc "The constellation includes the physical crane with its controller, a Python Physical Crane Interface, Control and Logging applications, human‑machine interface, a TimescaleDB container, an MQTT broker, a Grafana dashboard container, and two twin service containers (Trajectory Generator & Simulation) plus a Continuous Validation container, all orchestrated by Docker‑Compose and connected over a virtual bridge network."
]

instance life_cycle_stages : DTDFVocab:EvolutionStage [
    base:desc "The twin lifecycle covers design (CAD models and kinematic model), implementation (Python module gantrylib, database, dashboards), operation (real‑time monitoring and control), validation (continuous comparison), and education/research (iterative extension)."
]

instance fidelity_and_validity_considerations : DTDFVocab:FidelityConsideration [
    base:desc "Model fidelity relies on a kinematic representation of the crane and a physics‑based simulator; validation is performed by continuous monitoring of executed trajectories against simulation using a distance metric and a predefined threshold. Fault detection uses supervised time‑series classification to flag deviations, thereby maintaining model validity during operation."
]

instance dt_technical_connection : DTDFVocab:TechnicalConnection [
    base:desc "The physical system communicates with the twin via a USB serial connection to the Arduino; the Physical Crane Interface publishes data over MQTT (TCP) and writes to a TimescaleDB database (PostgreSQL protocol). The internal services communicate over MQTT on the same Docker network; the Grafana dashboard queries TimescaleDB over the database port. All connections use unencrypted TCP within the local machine."
]

instance dt_hosting_deployment : DTDFVocab:Deployment [
    base:desc "All twin services are deployed as Docker containers on a single host (personal computer). Docker‑Compose manages container lifecycle, image build, and network configuration. The repository is hosted on GitHub, while documentation is served via MkDocs on GitHub Pages."
]

instance standardization : DTDFVocab:Standardization [
    base:desc "The twin employs open‑source standards: MQTT (IEEE 802.15.4 analogue for messaging), PostgreSQL for time‑series storage, Docker for containerization, Grafana for monitoring, Autodesk Fusion 360 for CAD, Arcadia/Capella for MBSE modeling, KiCad for PCB design, Arduino for firmware. No specific twin standard is adhered to, but the architecture follows the C4 model and MBSE practices."
]
